# Prisma migrations are mandatory in PavleTekBackend

Any change to `prisma/schema.prisma` or the database structure MUST be applied via:

```bash
npx prisma migrate dev --name describe_your_change
```

**NEVER run `npx prisma db push` against this project's database**, even for "quick" experiments or prototyping.

## Why this rule exists

Production deploys run `npx prisma migrate deploy`, which only executes committed migration files. If you used `db push` locally and never created a migration, production and all other environments will silently miss the new columns/tables and the app will fail at runtime.

## Required workflow for schema changes

1. Edit `prisma/schema.prisma`.
2. Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name describe_your_change` (e.g. `add_quote_inquiries`).
3. Commit the generated `prisma/migrations/<timestamp>_<name>/migration.sql` together with the updated `schema.prisma`.

## Pre-push enforcement

The `.husky/pre-push` hook automatically runs:

- `npx prisma validate` — syntax check on schema.prisma
- `npx prisma generate` — verifies the generator compiles
- `node scripts/check-prisma-migration.js` — fails the push if schema.prisma was changed without a paired new migration directory

If the hook rejects your push, create the migration first, then push.

## When `db push` IS allowed

Only when the user **explicitly asks** for it (e.g. for a throwaway local branch experiment that will never be merged). Never as a substitute for `migrate dev` in feature branches.

## Summary

| Action | Command |
|---|---|
| Schema change | `npx prisma migrate dev --name <name>` |
| Deploy / production | `npx prisma migrate deploy` (already in `npm run migrate`) |
| `db push` | Only on explicit user request; never as default |
